SingleEvent.create(:id => 1865, :name => "2013", :description => "**Programm**\r\n \r\n- 09:00 Anmeldung / Eröffnung der Ausstellung\r\n- 09:30 Begrüßung durch Uwe Kammann, Direktor des Grimme-Instituts, und Angela Spizig, Bürgermeisterin der Stadt Köln\r\n- 09:50 Eröffnungsrede von Dr. Angelica Schwall-Düren, Ministerin für Bundesangelegenheiten, Europa und Medien des Landes Nordrhein-Westfalen\r\n- 10:05 Panel 1: „Erfolgreiche Frauen in den Medienbranchen“\r\n- 11:20 Kaffeepause\r\n- 11:45 Panel 2: „Ausbildung in der Medienbranche – Voraussetzungen, Erfahrungen, Bedingungen“\r\n- 12:45 Mittagessen / Besuch der Ausstellung\r\n- 13:45 Parallele Workshops: Workshop 1 „Journalismus“ mit Christina Wandt / WAZ und Priya Bathe / freie Journalistin // Workshop 2 „Social Media und Co.“ mit Julia Christophers / Turtle Entertainment und Katarina Peranic / Stiftung Bürgermut\r\n- 15:00 Uhr: Kaffeepause\r\n- 15:20 Parallele Workshops: Workshop 3 „Bewegte Bilder“ mit Katharina Tillmanns / Transmedia Autorin und Producerin sowie Bettina Braun / Filmemacherin // Workshop 4 „Medienberufe – ein Überblick“ mit Bettina Baum und Anne Schulz / Koordinationscentrum Ausbildung in Medienberufen (AIM) und Medienkarriere.nrw\r\n- 16:35 Ausklang – Gelegenheit zum Gespräch\r\n- 17:30 Ende der Veranstaltung\r\n\r\nDie Teilnahme ist kostenlos. Mehr Informationen zu der Veranstaltung im [Flyer](http://www.medienfrauen-nrw.de/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Medienfrauen_2013.pdf).", :event_id => 278, :occurrence => Wed, 13 Mar 2013 09:00:00 CET +01:00, :url => "http://www.medienfrauen-nrw.de/veranstaltungen/", :duration => 500, :full_day => false, :based_on_rule => false, :category_id => 5, :venue_id => 81, :use_venue_info_of_event => true)
SingleEvent.create(:id => 1856, :name => "Info Session: Developers/designers wanted for SWITCH Asia (EU project) web application", :description => "**Information:**\r\n\r\nThe SWITCH-Asia Network Facility is funded by the European Union to provide support to the knowledge sharing and dissemination and communication of SWITCH-Asia programme – an EU programme on Sustainable Consumption and Production in Asia (for more details see www.switch-asia.eu). In the project at present over 50 projects in Asia are active and for more effective and efficient knowledge sharing we want to develop a web-based exchange tool; o facilitate exchange of project outputs, knowledge, lessons learned and ideas. The online feature will enable continuous exchange beyond the dialogue happening offline at the Networking Events.\r\n\r\nDuring the meeting a short introduction will be given about the SWITCH-Asia Programme and more in-depth insight on how the web-application tool should look like and how its development is envisioned.\r\n\r\nA beta-version of the application should be available latest end of May, and therefore the work should commence as soon as possible. The indicative budget available for the work is 30.000 Euro (with some flexibility).\r\n\r\nThe Network Facility is looking for an organisation / a team of expert(s) with proven in-depth knowledge of:\r\n\r\n- solution design specifications, adequate for web development\r\n- definition of the logical and physical structure of the BIG BAZAAR websites and sub-pages;\r\n- definition and integration of the various required technological components;\r\n- development of web-enabled applications, from front-end to back-end systems.\r\n\r\nThey must have proven capacity in planning and performing usability tests, conceptual design of web interfaces Planning and performing usability test, conceptual design of web interfaces. The expert(s) must be proficient in English, speaking and writing, and must be available for communicating with the Network Facility Team in Germany (Wuppertal).\r\n\r\nFor everybody interested in this possible assignment and with adequate knowledge, please come and listen to the presentations and use the opportunity to ask questions on Wednesday March 13th from 10:30 till 12:30 at Clusterhaus, Im Klapperhof 7- 23 in Cologne. For those who unfortunately cannot be present at Wednesday, but are interested – we try to arrange also an on-line connection via Skype (but no guarantees can be made).\r\n\r\nFor more information beforehand please send an e-mail: [network.facility@scp-centre.org](network.facility@scp-centre.org)", :event_id => 274, :occurrence => Wed, 13 Mar 2013 10:30:00 CET +01:00, :url => "https://www.facebook.com/events/439132559500894/", :duration => 120, :full_day => false, :based_on_rule => false, :category_id => 2, :venue_id => 136, :use_venue_info_of_event => true)
SingleEvent.create(:id => 1849, :name => "Canvas day", :description => "The very unique five week pre-acceleration program Startup Weekend NEXT concludes on Wednesday 13.03.2013 with a Canvas Day - final presentations of 6 startup teams.\r\nWe are matching our efforts together with Startupbootcamp Open Pitch Day in Cologne and we are putting up for you an great networking event where you can meet the teams, the organizers and the mentors from NEXT Cologne and Startupbootcamp.\r\n\r\n**AGENDA**\r\n\r\n- 18:00 - 18:10 Intro\r\n- 18:10 - 18:20 NEXT Cologne\r\n- 18:20 - 20:00 Team Pitches\r\n- 20:00 - 20:15 NEXT and Startup scene in Cologne\r\n- 20:15 - open end Networking", :event_id => 194, :occurrence => Wed, 13 Mar 2013 18:00:00 CET +01:00, :url => "https://www.facebook.com/events/421023214654645/", :duration => 180, :full_day => false, :based_on_rule => false, :category_id => 2, :venue_id => 147, :use_venue_info_of_event => true)
